assets.name: Vas Cranii #750
assets.description:
*Though the wound is healed, a scar remains*

Vas Cranii (Skull Vases) is a collection of 7,117 unique themed art pieces made from more than 250 unique traits. The art aims to preserve a cultural heritage on the blockchain. Each piece has its unique meaning: The skull - representing its death as the language becomes a rarity and is slowly being forgotten. The orchid - which blooms with a multitude of color and variety represents how the language has evolved and influenced our modern languages. Each masterpiece has been carefully selected and engraved with one of over 250 unique and meaningful Latin phrases that we want to perpetuate on the blockchain as NFTs. Owning a piece of this collection not only gives you exclusive ownership of an exquisite piece of art but also lets you immortalize a piece of this beautiful language on the blockchain.

collection.description: Vas Cranii (Skull Vases) is a collection of 7,117 unique themed art pieces made from more than 250 unique traits. The art aims to preserve one important piece of history on the blockchain (The Latin Language). Each piece has its unique meaning: The skull - representing death of the language as it becomes a rarity and as it is slowly being forgotten. The orchid - which blooms with a multitude of color and variety represents how the language has evolved and influenced our modern day languages. Each masterpiece has been carefully selected and engraved with one of over 250 unique and meaningful Latin phrases that will be perpetuated on the blockchain as NFTs. Owning a piece of this collection not only gives you exclusive ownership of an exquisite piece of art but also lets you immortalize it and its deep meaning on the blockchain.

assets.name: The Asylum Project - Empty Bed
assets.description:
Selected artwork for the book "The Best of Photography 2014", included in the Black & White Collection at Musse du Louvre, Paris July 13th, 2015. 

Lier Psychiatric Hospital in Norway has a long history as an institution. The massive buildings house the memory of a grim chapter in Norwegian psychiatric history the authorities would rather forget. There is little available information about the former activities at Lier Hospital, but it is documented experiments that were carried out on this Norwegian mental hospital in the postwar period from 1945 to 1975. It's about the use of LSD, electroshock, brain research funded by the U.S. Department of Defense and drug research sponsored by major pharmaceutical companies. It is perhaps not surprising that they try to forget this place and the events taking place here. 

Lier Psychiatric Hospital was built in 1926 and had room for nearly 700 patients at the most. In 1986, many of the buildings were closed and abandoned and they still stand empty to this day. Some of the buildings are still in operation today for psychiatric patients. 

Unique and Exclusive High-Res Photography added to my existing limited edition fine art print collection from www.erikbrede.com. File Size: 4750x3166px 300dpi

collection.description: Collection of Black&White, Architecture, Infrared and Landscape Photography from Erik Brede Photography & Digital Art - www.erikbrede.com
collection.name: Bredes Photo Collection

collection.description:
What started out as doodles left on restaurant and bar receipts in 2015 is now a collection of 10,000 unique programmatically generated NFTs on the Ethereum blockchain. Based on the art of Arlo Eisenberg, Drug Receipts is founded on the principles of art, science, skepticism, subversion, and community.

Led by four main characters, Cap, Tabbi, Rex, and Syrin, Drug Receipts is at once irresistibly cute and also brazenly provocative. Drug Receipts does not take a position on whether drugs are good or bad. All of the characters are deliberately ambiguous—Illicit substances that can be used for healing or recreation. Responsibly or recklessly.

Drug Receipts is a defense of nuance. It is a prescription against polarization. Become a pusher of deeper and more thoughtful content. Trade in illicit conversations. Join the growing legion of Drug Snugglers and help spread Drug Receipts’ unique brand of mind-altering substance.
